untime path, not metadata generation. That log says the failing case is not a missing registration error; instead MockK’s Byte Buddy attachment path can throw `IllegalStateException: No compatible attachment provider is available` on GitHub runners. The preserved work appears to add a test-only fix in `MockkNativeImageSupport.kt` plus a regression test `MockkNativeImageSupportTest.kt`, and the same log says verification then passed with `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all`. `logs/io.mockk:mockk-agent-jvm:1.14.9/pr-review/codex_pr_review_6180.log` is also worth checking because the original PR passed normal native-image verification, which fits this being a future-defaults-only regression.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and review the test-only changes in `MockkNativeImageSupport.kt` and `MockkNativeImageSupportTest.kt`.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew clean test -Pcoordinates=io.mockk:mockk-agent-jvm:1.14.9 --stacktrace` with `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all` to confirm the failure mode locally.\\n3. If that reproduces cleanly, promote the preserved branch changes into a PR/manual fix; no metadata JSON change appears necessary.\"}}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
